## Milestone 1.B — Zone 2 · Explore Your Current State

### Dimensions
```
flex: defined in Milestone 1 layout
width: 88% of screen width, horizontally centered
```

### Typography
- Label "Explore your current state": section-label (see DESIGN.md)
- Chips: chip (see DESIGN.md)

### Label
- Text: "Explore your current state" with downward chevron on the right
- No container, no background, no border

### Chips surface
See DESIGN.md — Chips.

### Layer A
6 chips in a horizontal wrap:

```
"I'm feeling..." · "I want · I need" · "I'd like" · 
"I don't know" · "Something's off" · "Just here"
```

On chip tap: chip text deposits into chatbox input, 
Layer A disappears, Layer A.b appears in its place.

### Layer A.b — sub-chips per Layer A chip
```
"I'm feeling..."   → foggy · heavy · anxious · flat · absent
"Something's off"  → uneasy · irritable · tense · restless · hollow
"I don't know"     → numb · distant · lost · floating · unclear
"Just here"        → quiet · still · waiting · open · in-between
"I want · I need"  → opens chatbox directly, cursor ready, no sub-chips
"I'd like"         → opens chatbox directly, cursor ready, no sub-chips
```

Multiple chips (Layer A.b or Layer B) can be accumulated in chatbox 
input, separated by middle dot ( · ).

### Layer B
- Revealed below Layer A or A.b when "Name what you feel" label 
  is expanded via chevron
- 12 chips in a 3-column, 4-row CSS grid
- Placeholder chips: Anxious · Sad · Numb · Fragile · Restless · 
  Tender · Heavy · Scattered · Hollow · Raw · Tense · Lost

### Chip interaction with chatbox
