## Milestone 1.D — Zone 4 · Circle of Actions of Awareness

### Dimensions
```
flex: defined in Milestone 1 layout
width: 88% of screen width, horizontally centered
```

### Typography
- Category labels: section-label (see DESIGN.md)
- Micro-command labels: chip (see DESIGN.md)
- Session text and instructions: body text (see DESIGN.md)
- Central circle text: body text, centered (see DESIGN.md)

### Surface
- Central circle: large circular element, background #F5F5F3, 
  border: 1px solid #222220, no shadow
- Category icons arranged radially around the central circle
- Micro-command icons replace category icons on drag interaction

### Icons (mock — emoji placeholders, final version to be defined)
```
1. Breathwork  — 🫁
2. Stillness   — 🧠
3. Movement    — 🏃
4. Nature      — 🍀
5. Expression  — 🖊️
6. Water       — 🤲
7. Devotion    — 🧘
8. Environment — 🪷 (placeholder — final: custom line illustration)
```

### Interaction model
- Navigation language: drag and drop only — no clicking, no menus
- Drag Presence Circle toward category icon → category icons disappear, 
  micro-command icons appear in their place
- Drag toward micro-command → session launches or duration selector appears
- Nature is the sole exception (see Nature below)
- Drag implemented via HTML5 drag API or pointer events

### Core interaction modes

**Press and Hold — Presence & Gratitude Timer:**
```
- Press and hold Presence Circle for 2.3 seconds
- 2-minute timer activates
- Screen blurs — all surrounding elements soften (CSS backdrop-filter)
- Circular countdown ring appears around the circle (SVG stroke-dashoffset)
- Center text: "Stay in presence and gratitude in your mind and body"
- No further interaction during session
- On completion: blur lifts, screen returns to rest quietly, no prompt
```

**Drag and Drop — Micro-Action Navigation:**
Two gestures: drag to category, drag to micro-command.
Consistent pattern across all categories except Nature.

### Categories and micro-commands

**1. Breathwork**
```
Regulate · Activate · Ground · Open
(Physiological sigh / Kapalabhati burst / Box breathing / 4-7-8)
No duration selector — self-paced
Session screen: text only, minimal
```

**2. Stillness**
```
Guided · Unguided · Rest · Body scan
Duration selector: 2.5 / 6 / 10 / 20 minutes
Session begins immediately after duration selected
```

**3. Movement**
```
Strength · Jump & open · Shake · Mobility · Stretch
Duration selector: 2.5 / 6 / 10 / 20 minutes
Confirmation screen before session begins
Session screen: sequential text cues timed to duration
```

**4. Nature**
```
No sub-menu — exception to standard interaction pattern
On drag to Nature: 2.5–3 minute mobilization timer launches immediately
Timer clickable — user clicks to confirm they are moving
On confirmation or natural completion: invitation list appears
Invitation list: non-interactive, low contrast, generous spacing
Dismissed by single click anywhere
```

**5. Expression**
```
Write · Speak · Draw
No duration selector
Each launches 90-second mobilization timer
Write: instruction "pick up a pen and paper" — no in-app writing field
Speak: minimal recording interface — waveform and timer only, 
       nothing stored, recording released at session end
       (Web Audio API / MediaRecorder)
Draw: instruction "pick up a pencil or pen" — no in-app canvas
```

**6. Water**
```
Cold · Hot · Wash
Cold and Hot: 90-second mobilization timer, clickable to confirm arrival
Wash: no mobilization timer — immediate 2-minute timer on screen
Session screen: minimal orienting phrase, no enforced duration
```

**7. Devotion**
```
Recite · Chant · Pray · Sit in devotion
Duration selector: 2.5 / 6 / 10 / 20 minutes
Tradition-neutral language throughout
Session screen: minimal, dimmed, soft closing signal
```

**8. Environment**
```
Music · Arrange · Window
Concept: regulate through immediate physical surroundings
Content personalization: defined in future milestone
```

