## Milestone 1.2 — Zone & Component Interaction Behavior

### Zone 1 ↔ Zone 2: Chatbox & Explore Your Current State

**Text relation:**
```
- Clicking a chip deposits its text into the chatbox input
- Multiple chips can be accumulated in the input
- Each additional chip separated by middle dot ( · )
  example: "nervous · sensitive · discomfort"
- The AI responds to the combination as a whole
- User can edit, complete or extend the deposited text freely
- Double-clicking a chip sends the input directly
- On first chip click, display micro-hint below input: 
  "tap to add · double tap to send"
  Appears once, fades out after 3 seconds, never shown again
```

**Surface dimension relation:**
```
Default state:
  chatbox: flex 0.33
  Zone 2: visible

Zone 2 expanded (chips visible):
  chatbox: flex 0.33 (no resize)

On first message sent:
  chatbox: flex 0.95
  Zone 2: hidden
  (full-screen conversation mode)

On navigation away (tab switch):
  conversation auto-saved, state preserved on return

On conversation end (journal save or community share):
  chatbox resets to default
  Zone 2 returns visible
  new empty state displayed

Full-screen conversation mode — Zone 2 collapsed:
  chatbox:           flex 0.80
  gapChatboxToLabel: flex 0.03
  exploreLabel:      flex 0.03
  zone4Peek:         flex 0.07
  navigationBar:     flex 0.07

Full-screen conversation mode — Zone 2 expanded:
  chatbox:           flex 0.56
  gapChatboxToLabel: flex 0.03
  zone2Expanded:     flex 0.27
  zone4Peek:         flex 0.07
  navigationBar:     flex 0.07
```

### Zone 1 ↔ Zone 3: Chatbox & Inspire My Reflection

**Surface and Text relation:**
```
When Zone 3 expands:
  chatbox reduces to flex 0.13
  chatbox displays reduced empty state: "Check within yourself"
  chatbox remains active and clickable — clicking returns to default, 
  Zone 3 collapses

Below Zone 3 prompt: text entry area with blinking CSS cursor
  (animated via CSS: border-right blink animation)

On entry confirmed (Enter or send button):
  chatbox expands to flex 0.95
  Zone 3 prompt and user response appear as opening conversation lines
  Zone 2 and Zone 3 hidden

If user closes Zone 3 without responding:
  all zones return to default state

Zone 4 reduces to thin peek (flex 0.10) with upward chevron 
while Zone 3 is active

Collapse chevron on Zone 3 returns all zones to default at any moment
```

### Zone 1 ↔ Zone 4: Chatbox & Circle of Actions of Awareness

**Surface dimension relation:**
```
When Zone 4 expands:
  topGap:            flex 0.04
  chatbox:           flex 0.12
  gapChatboxToLabel: flex 0.03
  exploreLabel:      flex 0.03
  gapToInspire:      flex 0.04
  inspireLabel:      flex 0.05
  gapBelowInspire:   flex 0.04
  zone4Expanded:     flex 0.58
  navigationBar:     flex 0.07

Zone 2 and Zone 3: visible as collapsed labels only
Clicking Zone 1 chatbox collapses Zone 4, returns all zones to default,
chatbox becomes active
```

